{"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/matchinfoprotocol\/fetchall()"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"metadata":{"symbolKind":"method","extendedModule":"GLib","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"fetchAll"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"text":"UnsafeMutablePointer","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sp","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"text":"UnsafeMutablePointer","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sp","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"gchar"},{"text":">?>!","kind":"text"}],"title":"fetchAll()","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Method","externalID":"s:4GLib17MatchInfoProtocolPAAE8fetchAllSpySpys4Int8VGSgGSgyF"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Bundles up pointers to each of the matching substrings from a match"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"and stores them in an array of gchar pointers. The first element in","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the returned array is the match number 0, i.e. the entire matched"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"text.","type":"text"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"fetchAll","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sp","text":"UnsafeMutablePointer","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sp","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"UnsafeMutablePointer"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar","text":"gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":">?>!","kind":"text"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If a sub pattern didn’t match anything (e.g. sub pa